sec.p:
Laboratory testing was regularly performed. Preoperative Hb, Hct, CK and CRP were recorded at admission. Postoperative Hb, Hct, CK and CRP were detected on the 2nd day after operation. No blood transfusion was required during or after operation, and thus TBL was calculated based on the perioperative change of Hct (Nash et al., 2016; Gross, 1983). 
