\begin{document}
\begin{eqnarray*}\mathrm{TBL}(\mathrm{ml})=\text{Patient blood volume}(\mathrm{PBV},\mathrm{ml})\times \frac{(\text{Hctpre}-\text{Hctpost})}{(\text{Hctpre}+\text{Hctpost})} \times 2. \end{eqnarray*}\end{document}TBLml=Patient blood volumePBV,ml×Hctpre−HctpostHctpre+Hctpost×2.
In this calculation, Hctpre and Hctpost are short for pre- and postoperative Hct, respectively.

