$\mathrm{PBV} \left( \mathrm{ml} \right) =(\mathrm{k}1\times \text{height}{ \left( \mathrm{m} \right) }^{3}+\mathrm{k}2\times \text{weight}(\mathrm{Kg})+\mathrm{k}3)\times 1000$\end{document}PBVml=k1×heightm3+k2×weightKg+k3×1000. (k1= 0.3561, k2= 0.03308, and k3= 0.1833, for women; k1= 0.3669, k2= 0.03219, and k3= 0.6041, for men) (Nadler, Hidalgo & Bloch, 1962).
